Description: Landscape with the flight into Egypt, with Joseph in the right foreground helping Mary who holds the Child into a punt, while the donkey grazes; in the background a town and two pyramids; after Carracci Etching
Curator's comments: It is not certain which of the Carracci was supposed to have made this composition, but it is currently placed under Agostino.
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Sir Hans Sloane (with Philipe's large pencilled initials HS)
Acquisition notes: Although Philipe used the Cracherode blindstamp with the initials CMC, he has written HS in bold pencil on the verso
